chav1961.funnypro.core.interfaces

Interface IResolvable

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    StandardResolver

    public interface IResolvable

    This interface describes any external predicates/operators plugin. Life cycle of every plugin is:

    Plugin loading

    Load plugin and call its onLoad(LoggerFacade, Properties, IFProEntitiesRepo) method. Common practice is to register all predicates and operators that the given plugin supports (see StandardResolver class source code for example). The plugin also can create any structure for it's own purposes and return it as a result of calling this method. This structure will be passed to all other methods in the 'global' parameter.

    Resolving predicate

    A life cycle to resolve one of the registered predicates (see below)

    Plugin removing

    Remove plugin and free it's resources. Common practice is to deregister all the registered predicates and operators and free global structure, created by onLoad(LoggerFacade, Properties, IFProEntitiesRepo) method.

    The life cycle of the resolving predicate is:

    Preparing resolving

    Prepare resolving process and call IResolvable#beforeCall(Object, IFProGlobalStack, List, IFProCallback) method. Plugin can create any structure for it's own purposes and return it as a result of calling method. This structure will be passed to all other methods in the 'local' parameter.

    The first resolution

    Forward resolution of the predicate/operator by calling firstResolve(Object, Object, IFProEntity). Returns IResolvable.ResolveRC instance as a result.

    The backtrace

    This is an optional step and executes only if the first resolution was successful. Calling nextResolve(Object, Object, IFProEntity) method. Returns IResolvable.ResolveRC instance as a result.

    End resolving

    Finish resolving the given predicate/operator and call endResolve(Object, Object, IFProEntity).

    Unprepare resolving

    Calling afterCall(Object, Object). Common practice is to free structures returning by IResolvable#beforeCall(Object, IFProGlobalStack, List, IFProCallback) method

    Since:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Alexander Chernomyrdin aka chav1961
